<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/packaging/2011/10/nuspec.xsd">
    <metadata>
        <id>libVPNET</id>
        <version>0.3.0-pre</version>
        <title>libVirtualParadise.NET</title>
        <authors>Roy Curtis</authors>
        <projectUrl>https://github.com/RoyCurtis/libVPNET</projectUrl>
        <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
        <description>Alternative wrapper to the Virtual Paradise C SDK. Allows for the creation of bots to interact with 3D virtual worlds.

Features a more C#-centric design, including structs and utility classes useful for VP/VR concepts.

The native libraries are packaged into the assembly and are automatically unpacked on use. Supported architectures:

* x86-64 Linux (CentOS)
* x86 Windows

This library itself is compiled as x86 only (but is known to work on Mono with the 64bit libs).</description>
        <summary>Alternative library for writing Virtual Paradise bots</summary>
        <releaseNotes>0.3.0-pre - Infinite call loop fixes for ConsoleMessage, removed some ConsoleMessage methods for simplicity

0.2.3-pre - Fixed null object data bug and potential memory leaks

0.2.2-pre - Added NodeSet callback to terrain

0.2.1-pre - Updated to VP SDK 0.3.37 / r1093 featuring:
* Ability to send URLs to clients to open in a 3D overlay or external browser
* Single-object query by ID and callback
* Disconnection event reasons

0.2.0-pre - Mostly rewritten to formalize an API, complete implementation of all bot-accessible features

0.1.0-pre - Forked and adapted from official .NET wrapper</releaseNotes>
        <language>en-GB</language>
        <dependencies>
            <dependency id="Nexus" version="2.1.0" />
        </dependencies>
    </metadata>
    <files>
        <file src="Build\VP.NET\libVPNET.dll" target="lib\net40\libVPNET.dll" />
        <file src="Build\VP.NET\libVPNET.pdb" target="lib\net40\libVPNET.pdb" />
        <file src="Build\VP.NET\libVPNET.xml" target="lib\net40\libVPNET.xml" />
    </files>
</package>